    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-11-24T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-11-24T11:00:00-05:00" n="805"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d805">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.2331/120: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Peru</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-11-24T12:00:00-04:00"
                            >November 24, 1938—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 2:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>84. Referring to the Embassy’s despatches 741 and 763<note n="40"
                        xml:id="d805fn40">Latter not printed.</note> November 9th and 19th
                    respectively. Dr. Concha informed me orally yesterday that Peru will agree to
                    limited exceptions in the case of Chile, but that the list of exceptions to be
                    proposed and now being prepared will be long, and on the condition that there be
                    an exchange of letters or informal notes in addition to the trade agreement, by
                    which the United States will undertake to reconsider the exceptions listed in
                    the trade agreement in the case of Chile, in the event that the Chilean demands
                    upon Peru in the course of the negotiation of the new Peruvian-Chilean
                    commercial treaty are of such a nature as to necessitate such
                    reconsideration.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
